#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Database"
msgstr "Podatkovna baza"

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using relational databases"
msgstr "Uporaba relacijskih podatkovnih baz"

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since release 1.0, &kmymoney; allows you to hold your data in a relational "
"database. One of the advantages of using this industry-standard format is "
"that it may allow you to view your data using one of the graphic front ends "
"such as <trademark>OpenOffice.org</trademark> or <trademark>LibreOffice</"
"trademark>, or perhaps in some format that &kmymoney; currently doesn't "
"provide. Also, a little knowledge of <acronym><ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/SQL\">SQL</ulink> </acronym> (<quote>Structured Query "
"Language</quote>, the language used world-wide to access relational "
"databases) should enable you more easily to export data to an external "
"program, for example, a budgeting application."
msgstr ""
"Od izdaje 1.0 je &kmymoney; omogoča shranjevanje vaših podatkov v relacijski "
"bazi podatkov. Ena od prednosti uporabe tega industrijskega standardnega "
"formata je, da vam lahko omogoča ogled podatkov z uporabo enega od grafičnih "
"vmesnikov, kot je <trademark>OpenOffice.org</trademark> ali "
"<trademark>LibreOffice</trademark>, ali morda v neki obliki, ki jo "
"&kmymoney; trenutno ne zagotavlja. Prav tako malo znanja o <acronym><ulink "
"url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQL\">SQL</ulink> </acronym> "
"(<quote>Structured Query Language</quote>, jezik, ki se uporablja po vsem "
"svetu za dostop do relacijskih baz podatkov), bi vam moral omogočiti lažji "
"izvoz podatkov v zunanji program, na primer v aplikacijo za proračun."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although most relational database systems allow concurrent access to a "
"database by more than one user, this is not possible with &kmymoney;. Even "
"though &kmymoney; can store its data in a relational database, it actually "
"uses the database as just a different type of file storage. When you open "
"your file, the program reads all of the data from the database. As you work "
"with your data, the changes are made only to the internal storage; they are "
"not immediately written back to the database. Only when you save your data "
"does &kmymoney; write the entire file back to the database."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav večina sistemov relacijskih baz podatkov dovoljuje sočasen dostop do "
"baze podatkov več kot enemu uporabniku, to ni mogoče pri &kmymoney;. Čeprav "
"&kmymoney; lahko shrani svoje podatke v relacijsko zbirko podatkov, dejansko "
"uporablja zbirko podatkov le kot drugo vrsto shranjevanja datotek. Ko "
"odprete datoteko, program prebere vse podatke iz baze podatkov. Ko delate s "
"svojimi podatki, se spremembe izvajajo samo v notranjem pomnilniku; niso "
"takoj zapisani nazaj v bazo podatkov. Samo ko shranite svoje podatke, "
"&kmymoney; zapišite celotno datoteko nazaj v bazo podatkov."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There have been requests for &kmymoney; to update the database for each data "
"change, but this would require a significant change to the entire way the "
"program manages its internal data structures, so this is extremely unlikely "
"to happen in the foreseeable future."
msgstr ""
"Obstajajo zahteve za &kmymoney; posodobiti bazo podatkov za vsako spremembo "
"podatkov, vendar bi to zahtevalo znatno spremembo celotnega načina, kako "
"program upravlja svoje notranje podatkovne strukture, zato je zelo malo "
"verjetno, da se bo to zgodilo v bližnji prihodnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparation"
msgstr "Priprava"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To access the database, &kmymoney; uses the SQL module supplied by &Qt; "
"Software as part of their &Qt; programming system. This module supports many "
"database systems through a collection of drivers. &Qt; has drivers for a "
"large number of open source and proprietary relational database systems, "
"including <trademark>MySQL</trademark>, PostgreSQL, and SQLCipher. The "
"module also supports some 'heavier', more industrial, systems such as "
"<trademark class=\"registered\">Oracle</trademark> and IBM <trademark class="
"\"registered\">DB2</trademark>."
msgstr ""
"Za dostop do baze podatkov &kmymoney; uporablja modul SQL, ki ga nudi &Qt; "
"Programska oprema kot del njihovega programskega sistema &Qt;. Ta modul "
"podpira številne sisteme baz podatkov prek zbirke gonilnikov. &Qt; ima "
"gonilnike za veliko število odprtokodnih in lastniških sistemov relacijskih "
"baz podatkov, vključno z <trademark>MySQL</trademark>, PostgreSQL in "
"SQLCipher. Modul podpira tudi nekatere 'težje', bolj industrijske sisteme, "
"kot sta <trademark class=\"registered\">Oracle</trademark> in IBM <trademark "
"class=\"registered\">DB2</trademark>."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Previous versions of &kmymoney; supported <ulink url=\"https://www.sqlite.org"
"\">SQLite</ulink>. This has been replaced with support for <ulink url="
"\"https://www.zetetic.net/sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</ulink>, which is a "
"standalone fork of the SQLite database library that adds 256 bit AES "
"encryption and other security features. The SQLCipher driver will read "
"existing SQLite files. See the section below on <link linkend=\"details."
"database.sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</link> for more details."
msgstr ""
"Prejšnje različice &kmymoney; so podpirale <ulink url=\"https://www.sqlite."
"org\">SQLite</ulink>. To je bilo nadomeščeno s podporo za <ulink url="
"\"https://www.zetetic.net/sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</ulink>, ki je samostojna "
"razcepka knjižnice zbirke podatkov SQLite, ki dodaja 256-bitno šifriranje "
"AES in drugo varnost funkcije. Gonilnik SQLCipher bo prebral obstoječe "
"datoteke SQLite. Za več podrobnosti glejte spodnji razdelek o <link linkend="
"\"details.database.sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the exception of SQLCipher, these systems use a client/server model, "
"where the 'client' software sits on 'your' machine, while the server lives "
"on the same machine as the database itself, which may be elsewhere on a "
"network. Of course, in the normal scenario for a personal finance "
"application such as &kmymoney;, 'your' machine can act as both client and "
"server. Your first task therefore, having decided which database system you "
"wish to use, is to install the client, and most probably server, software."
msgstr ""
"Z izjemo SQLCipherja ti sistemi uporabljajo model odjemalec/strežnik, kjer "
"je programska oprema 'odjemalec' na 'vašem' računalniku, medtem ko strežnik "
"živi na istem računalniku kot baza podatkov, ki je lahko drugje v omrežju. "
"Seveda lahko v običajnem scenariju za aplikacijo za osebne finance, kot je "
"&kmymoney;, 'vaš' stroj deluje kot odjemalec in strežnik. Ko se torej "
"odločite, kateri sistem baze podatkov želite uporabiti, je vaša prva naloga "
"namestitev odjemalske in najverjetneje strežniške programske opreme."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition to the database software itself, you must also install the "
"corresponding &Qt; driver module. Most &Linux; distributions will include "
"driver modules for the more popular databases. Otherwise, check with the "
"<ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">&Qt; software web site</ulink> and search "
"for <quote>SQL drivers</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Poleg same programske opreme baze podatkov morate namestiti tudi ustrezen "
"gonilniški modul &Qt;. Večina distribucij &Linux; bodo vključevale module "
"gonilnikov za bolj priljubljene zbirke podatkov. V nasprotnem primeru "
"preverite s <ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">&Qt; spletno mesto programske "
"opreme</ulink> in poiščite <quote>gonilnike SQL</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SQLCipher and SQLite do not operate on a client/server model; each database "
"is held in a regular file, local or remote, accessed using the normal "
"methods supplied by the underlying operating system. In this case, "
"therefore, there is only one software package and the driver to install. "
"Also, some of the following information, particularly that related to "
"administration, may not apply."
msgstr ""
"SQLCipher in SQLite ne delujeta na modelu odjemalec/strežnik; vsaka zbirka "
"podatkov je shranjena v običajni datoteki, lokalni ali oddaljeni, do katere "
"se dostopa z običajnimi metodami, ki jih ponuja osnovni operacijski sistem. "
"V tem primeru je torej na voljo samo en programski paket in gonilnik za "
"namestitev. Tudi nekatere od naslednjih informacij, zlasti tiste, ki se "
"nanašajo na administracijo, morda ne veljajo."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Administration"
msgstr "Administracija"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Looking after databases is a little more complex than dealing with regular "
"files. Each system has different methods for performing those necessary "
"administrative tasks such as creating databases, assigning permissions to "
"various users, or producing backups. Describing these tasks is outside the "
"scope of this manual, but all of the supported products provide "
"comprehensive reference documentation, and a quick search of the web will "
"point you at many tutorials on the subject."
msgstr ""
"Skrb za baze podatkov je nekoliko bolj zapletena kot obravnava običajnih "
"datotek. Vsak sistem ima različne metode za izvajanje tistih potrebnih "
"administrativnih nalog, kot je ustvarjanje baz podatkov, dodeljevanje "
"dovoljenj različnim uporabnikom ali izdelava varnostnih kopij. Opisovanje "
"teh nalog je izven obsega tega priročnika, vendar vsi podprti izdelki "
"zagotavljajo izčrpno referenčno dokumentacijo in hitro iskanje po spletu vas "
"bo usmerilo na številne vadnice na to temo."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating the database"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje baze podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmymoney; includes SQL code to create an initial database to hold your data "
"if one doesn't exist. However, it is strongly recommended that you pre-"
"create a database, because most of the products provide a number of options "
"which may be relevant. One that may be of particular importance to some "
"would be the designation of the character set (&eg;, UTF-8) to be used for "
"text fields."
msgstr ""
"&kmymoney; vključuje kodo SQL za ustvarjanje začetne baze podatkov za "
"shranjevanje vaših podatkov, če ta ne obstaja. Vendar je zelo priporočljivo, "
"da predhodno ustvarite zbirko podatkov, ker večina izdelkov ponuja številne "
"možnosti, ki so lahko pomembne. Ena, ki je lahko za nekatere še posebej "
"pomembna, bi bila določitev nabora znakov (&eg; UTF-8), ki se uporablja za "
"besedilna polja."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At this time, you will also need to specify permissions for various users to "
"perform different operations on the database. In most systems, the user who "
"creates the database will be automatically assigned all permissions, but "
"this is an area in which the documentation should be consulted."
msgstr ""
"V tem času boste morali določiti tudi dovoljenja za različne uporabnike za "
"izvajanje različnih operacij v bazi podatkov. V večini sistemov bodo "
"uporabniku, ki ustvari zbirko podatkov, samodejno dodeljena vsa dovoljenja, "
"vendar je to področje, na katerem je treba pregledati dokumentacijo."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For your first use of the database, and occasionally at other times when the "
"database layout changes, you will need permission (also called privileges) "
"to create and alter tables and views (see next paragraph.) There may be "
"different names for the permission/privilege in different systems, but "
"something like <literal>CREATE</literal> and <literal>ALTER</literal> should "
"be commonplace. For normal running, you will need to be able to read and "
"write records; these are normally defined in SQL as <literal>SELECT</"
"literal>, <literal>INSERT</literal>, <literal>UPDATE</literal>, and "
"<literal>DELETE</literal> permissions."
msgstr ""
"Za vašo prvo uporabo baze podatkov in občasno, ko se spremeni postavitev "
"baze podatkov, boste potrebovali dovoljenje (imenovano tudi pravica) za "
"ustvarjanje in spreminjanje tabel in pogledov (glejte naslednji odstavek.) "
"Za dovoljenje/imajo se lahko različna imena. privilegij v različnih "
"sistemih, vendar bi moralo biti nekaj, kot je <literal>CREATE</literal> in "
"<literal>ALTER</literal>, običajno. Za normalno delovanje boste morali znati "
"brati in pisati zapise; ta so v SQL običajno definirana kot dovoljenja "
"<literal>SELECT</literal>, <literal>INSERT</literal>, <literal>UPDATE</"
"literal> in <literal>DELETE</literal>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating Tables"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje tabel"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On your first use, &kmymoney; will attempt to create the necessary table "
"structures. In order to achieve the maximum compatibility between various "
"database types, only a subset of common data types are used. There may "
"nevertheless be situations where a particular type is not supported, and in "
"this case, provision has been made to generate the SQL code necessary to "
"create the tables. This code can then be modified as required and used to "
"create the tables outside of &kmymoney;. Should you find yourself in this "
"situation, help can usually be obtained from one of the channels listed in "
"the section on <link linkend=\"firsttime.contact\">Getting Help</link>. See "
"<link linkend=\"details.database.generatesql\">Manual Database Creation</"
"link> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Ob prvi uporabi &kmymoney; bo poskušal ustvariti potrebne strukture tabel. "
"Da bi dosegli največjo možno združljivost med različnimi vrstami podatkovnih "
"baz, se uporablja le podmnožica skupnih tipov podatkov. Kljub temu lahko "
"pride do situacij, ko določen tip ni podprt, in v tem primeru je bila "
"poskrbljeno za ustvarjanje kode SQL, ki je potrebna za ustvarjanje tabel. To "
"kodo lahko nato po potrebi spremenite in uporabite za ustvarjanje tabel "
"zunaj &kmymoney;. Če se znajdete v tej situaciji, lahko običajno dobite "
"pomoč na enem od kanalov, navedenih v razdelku <link linkend=\"firsttime."
"contact\">Iskanje pomoči</link>. Za več informacij glejte <link linkend="
"\"details.database.generatesql\">Ročno ustvarjanje baze podatkov</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Database"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje baze podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using &kmymoney;, open or import an existing data file, or create a new one. "
"Then select <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save as "
"Database</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Select <guilabel>SQL</"
"guilabel> from the <guilabel>Storage type to use for your data</guilabel> "
"dropdown, and click <guibutton>OK</guibutton>. You will then see the "
"following dialog:"
msgstr ""
"Z &kmymoney; odprite ali uvozite obstoječo podatkovno datoteko ali ustvarite "
"novo. Nato izberite menijski element <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Shrani kot zbirko podatkov</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. "
"Izberite <guilabel>SQL</guilabel> v spustnem meniju <guilabel>Vrsta "
"shranjevanja za vaše podatke</guilabel> in kliknite <guibutton>V redu</"
"guibutton>. Nato boste videli naslednje pogovorno okno:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: details-database.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>creating a database</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>ustvarjanje baze podatkov</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: details-database.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>creating a database</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>ustvarjanje baze podatkov</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Complete the fields appropriate to the database type you have selected (as "
"usual, mandatory fields will be highlighted) and click <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> to create the database."
msgstr ""
"Izpolnite polja, ki ustrezajo vrsti podatkovne baze, ki ste jo izbrali (kot "
"običajno bodo obvezna polja označena) in kliknite <guibutton>V redu</"
"guibutton>, da ustvarite bazo podatkov."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "Database Type"
msgstr "Vrsta baze podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This dropdown lists all the &Qt; SQL drivers installed on your system. "
"Select the driver for your database type. If the one you want is not in the "
"list, you need to install the appropriate driver. See your distribution "
"documentation, or visit the <ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">&Qt; software "
"web site</ulink> and search for 'SQL drivers'."
msgstr ""
"V tem polju so navedeni vsi gonilniki &Qt; SQL, nameščeni v vašem sistemu. "
"Izberite gonilnik za svojo vrsto baze podatkov. Če tistega, ki ga želite, ni "
"na seznamu, morate namestiti ustrezen gonilnik. Oglejte si distribucijsko "
"dokumentacijo ali obiščite <ulink url=\"https://www.qt.io/\">&Qt; spletno "
"mesto programske opreme</ulink> in poiščite 'gonilnike SQL'."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "File (SQLite/SQLCipher only)"
msgstr "Datoteka (samo SQLite/SQLCipher)"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SQLCipher has one database per file so enter the filename in which you wish "
"to create the database. To browse the file system, click the icon to the "
"right of the filename. For SQLCipher databases, the <guilabel>Database Name</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Host name</guilabel>, <guilabel>Username</guilabel> "
"fields are not relevant. The SQLCipher file must have the appropriate read/"
"write permissions set by the underlying file system to enable the "
"appropriate access for the currently logged-in user."
msgstr ""
"SQLCipher ima eno bazo podatkov na datoteko, zato vnesite ime datoteke, v "
"kateri želite ustvariti bazo podatkov. Če želite brskati po datotečnem "
"sistemu, kliknite ikono desno od imena datoteke. Za baze podatkov SQLCipher "
"polja <guilabel>Ime baze podatkov</guilabel>, <guilabel>Ime gostitelja</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Uporabniško ime</guilabel> niso pomembna. Datoteka "
"SQLCipher mora imeti ustrezna dovoljenja za branje/pisanje, ki jih nastavi "
"osnovni datotečni sistem, da omogoči ustrezen dostop za trenutno "
"prijavljenega uporabnika."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The creators of <ulink url=\"https://www.zetetic.net/sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</"
"ulink> released version 4.0 in November, 2018. However, many &kmymoney; "
"users, especially those who do not upgrade very often, or who use LTS (Long "
"Term Support) &Linux; distributions, may still be using a database created "
"with version 3 of SQLCipher. At some point, usually after upgrading "
"&kmymoney; or their distribution, they find they are unable to open their "
"database, with an error that is not particularly informative or useful. What "
"is required in this case is to upgrade the database itself from version 3 to "
"version 4. Instructions for this can be found on the <ulink url=\"https://"
"discuss.zetetic.net/t/upgrading-to-sqlcipher-4/3283\">SQLCipher website</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarjalci <ulink url=\"https://www zetatic.net/sqlcipher\">SQLCipher</"
"ulink> so izdali različico 4.0 novembra 2018. Vendar je veliko uporabnikov "
"&kmymoney;ja, zlasti tisti, ki ne nadgrajujejo zelo pogosto ali uporabljajo "
"LTS (dolgoročno podporo) distribucij &Linux;a, morda še vedno uporablja bazo "
"podatkov, ustvarjeno z različico 3 SQLCipherja. Na neki točki, običajno po "
"nadgradnji &kmymoney; ali njihove distribucije, ugotovijo, da ne morejo "
"odpreti svoje baze podatkov, z napako, ki ni posebej informativna ali "
"uporabna. V tem primeru je potrebno nadgraditi samo bazo podatkov iz "
"različice 3 na različico 4. Navodila za to lahko najdete na <ulink url="
"\"https://discuss.zetetic.net/t/upgrading-to-sqlcipher- 4/3283\">spletnem "
"mestu SQLCipher</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid "Database name (others)"
msgstr "Ime baze podatkov (drugo)"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default database name is <literal>KMyMoney</literal>, but you may choose "
"some other name if you like. For some database types, &kmymoney; may not be "
"able to create the database, so it must be pre-created using the appropriate "
"administrative procedure. However, &kmymoney; will usually be able to create "
"all table structures where necessary. If not, you can create them yourself. "
"See <link linkend=\"details.database.generatesql\">Manual Database Creation</"
"link> for more information."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto ime baze podatkov je <literal>KMyMoney</literal>, vendar lahko "
"izberete drugo ime, če želite. Za nekatere vrste baz podatkov &kmymoney; "
"baze podatkov morda ne bo mogel ustvariti, zato jo je treba predhodno "
"ustvariti z ustreznim administrativnim postopkom. Vendar &kmymoney; bo "
"običajno lahko ustvaril vse strukture tabel, kjer je to potrebno. Če ne, jih "
"lahko ustvarite sami. Za več informacij glejte <link linkend=\"details."
"database.generatesql\">Ročno ustvarjanje baze podatkov</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "Host name"
msgstr "Ime gostitelja"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the average user, the default name of <quote>localhost</quote>, being "
"the machine you are currently using, is correct. For networked databases, "
"enter the connected host name of the database server."
msgstr ""
"Za povprečnega uporabnika je privzeto ime <quote>localhost</quote> pravilno, "
"saj je stroj, ki ga trenutno uporabljate. Za omrežne baze podatkov vnesite "
"ime povezanega gostitelja strežnika baze podatkov."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid "User name and password"
msgstr "Uporabniško ime in geslo"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check the permissions set up on your database, or contact the database "
"administrator, for the correct values to use here. The user name must be "
"capable of selecting, inserting, updating, and deleting records. If the user "
"name is the same as your login name, a password is not normally required."
msgstr ""
"Preverite dovoljenja, nastavljena za vašo zbirko podatkov, ali se obrnite na "
"skrbnika baze podatkov za pravilne vrednosti, ki jih boste tukaj uporabili. "
"Uporabniško ime mora omogočati izbiro, vstavljanje, posodabljanje in "
"brisanje zapisov. Če je uporabniško ime enako vašemu prijavnemu imenu, geslo "
"običajno ni potrebno."

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accessing your data"
msgstr "Dostop do vaših podatkov"

#. Tag: title
#: details-database.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Table design"
msgstr "Oblikovanje tabele"

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To access your data in &kmymoney;, use the <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Open Database</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item. "
"This will open a dialog similar to the above."
msgstr ""
"Za dostop do svojih podatkov v &kmymoney; uporabite menijsko postavko "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Odpri zbirko podatkov</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice>. To bo odprlo pogovorno okno, podobno zgornjemu."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you created your database by first opening a file, and then doing "
"<guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem> and choosing "
"<guilabel>SQL</guilabel> as described above, then any subsequent changes to "
"your data are saved only in the database, not in the file. This means that "
"you can use the file as a backup or snapshot of your data at a particular "
"time. To make a new backup like this, open your database, choose the "
"<menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Save As...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item, choose <guilabel>XML</guilabel> as the storage type, "
"and giving an appropriate file name. Remember to re-open your database, so "
"&kmymoney; does not continue to use the file."
msgstr ""
"Če ste svojo zbirko podatkov ustvarili tako, da ste najprej odprli datoteko "
"in nato naredili <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Shrani</"
"guimenuitem> in izbrali <guilabel>SQL</guilabel>, kot je opisano zgoraj, se "
"bodo vse nadaljnje spremembe vaših podatkov shranjevali samo v bazi "
"podatkov, ne v datoteki. To pomeni, da lahko datoteko ob določenem času "
"uporabite kot varnostno kopijo ali posnetek svojih podatkov. Če želite "
"narediti novo varnostno kopijo, kot je ta, odprite bazo podatkov, izberite "
"menijski element <menuchoice> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Shrani kot...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, izberite "
"<guilabel>XML</guilabel> kot vrsto shranjevanja in podajte ustrezno ime "
"datoteke. Ne pozabite znova odpreti svoje zbirke podatkov, tako da "
"&kmymoney; ne nadaljuje z uporabo datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To access your data in other formats, you will need to know a little about "
"how it is held in relational databases. By far the easiest way to get a feel "
"for this is to open the database in a front-end such as "
"<trademark>OpenOffice.org</trademark>. This provides a list of the various "
"tables which make up the database, and enables you to see the layout of each "
"of them."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dostopati do svojih podatkov v drugih formatih, boste morali "
"vedeti nekaj o tem, kako se hranijo v relacijskih zbirkah podatkov. Daleč "
"najlažji način, da dobite občutek za to, je, da odprete bazo podatkov v "
"sprednjem delu, kot je <trademark>OpenOffice.org</trademark>. To ponuja "
"seznam različnih tabel, ki sestavljajo bazo podatkov, in vam omogoča, da "
"vidite postavitev vsake od njih."

#. Tag: para
#: details-database.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To extract data, &eg;, into a spreadsheet or external file, it is almost "
"invariably necessary to select linked data from more than one table. This is "
"done by <quote>joining</quote> the tables, using a field which is common to "
"them. You can find a lot more information about how this is done from the "
"online database tutorials mentioned above. The following table lists the "
"fields used to define these inter-table relationships."
msgstr ""
"Za pridobivanje podatkov, &eg; v preglednico ali zunanjo datoteko, je skoraj "
"vedno potrebno izbrati povezane podatke iz več kot ene tabele. To naredite "
"tako, da tabele <quote>združite</quote> z uporabo polja, ki jim je skupno. "
"Veliko več informacij o tem, kako se to naredi, lahko najdete v zgoraj "
"omenjenih vadnicah za spletno bazo podatkov. Naslednja tabela navaja polja, "
"ki se uporabljajo za definiranje teh odnosov med tabelami."

